title: Australia Inflation Expectations
description: Inflation Expectations in Australia increased to 6 percent in November from 5.40 percent in October of 2022. Inflation Expectations in Australia averaged 4.34 percent from 1995 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 8.60 percent in July of 2008 and a record low of 2.80 percent in September of 2013. In Australia, Melbourne Institute Inflation Expectations survey measures consumersâ€™ median expectations for price growth over the coming 12 months.
